  "articleSummary": "This tutorial explains how to secure a Docker host on Debian/Ubuntu using UFW (Uncomplicated Firewall). It provides step-by-step commands to set default deny policies, allow specific inbound and outbound traffic (SSH, HTTP, HTTPS, Docker networking), and forward ports to containerized applications. The guide emphasizes caution to avoid locking out SSH access and includes instructions for testing the firewall with nmap. The intended audience is system administrators or DevOps engineers managing Docker servers.",
